#use wml::debian::cdimage title="Downloading Debian CD images via HTTP/FTP" BARETITLE=true

<p><strong>Please do not download CD images with your web browser the way
you download other files!</strong> The reason is that if your download
aborts, most browsers do not allow you to resume from the point where it
failed.</p>

<p>Instead, please use a tool that supports resuming. Under Unix,
you can use "<tt>wget&nbsp;-c&nbsp;</tt><i>URL</i>" or
"<tt>curl&nbsp;-C&nbsp;-&nbsp;</tt><i>URL</i>". Note that some
versions of wget do not support downloading DVD-size images.
Under Windows, you might want to try
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/filezilla/">FileZilla</a>
(FTP) or <a href="http://www.freshdevices.com/freshdown.html">Fresh
Download</a> (HTTP).</p>

<p>The following Debian CD images are available for
download:</p>

<ul>

  <li>Official CD images of the "stable" release - 
  <a href="#stable">see below</a></li>

  <li>Official CD images of the "testing" distribution
  (<em>regenerated weekly</em>) - <a href="#testing">see below</a></li>

</ul>

<p>Be sure to have a look at the
<a href="$(HOME)/releases/stable/installmanual">detailed information
about the installation process</a>.</p>

<hr>

<h2><a name="stable">Official CD images of the "stable" releases</a></h2>

<p>Note that <strong>some mirrors are not up to date</strong> -
before downloading, check the version number of the images is the
same as the one listed <a href="../#latest">on this site</a>!</p>

<p><b>If in doubt, use the <a href="http://cdimage.debian.org/debian-cd/">primary
CD image server</a>.</b></p>

#use wml::debian::countries
